      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "The problem I'm trying to solve here is being able to set `prune=` in QT (#13043) without causing errors if the user later launches `bitcoind`, or if the user resets their QT settings (at which point they'd get locked out).\r\n\r\nAnother approach could be to reinterpret `prune=0` to mean \"you can't prune now, but it's OK if things were pruned in the past (fHavePruned=true)\".\r\n\r\nA similar problem exists for txindex, but that's solved by #13033, which no longer wipes the transaction index if you launch with `txindex=0`.",
      "created_at" : "2018-04-25T10:39:03Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/13029#issuecomment-384242859",
